⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of The Crossroads Confession
node CRP · CRP · ⟦The Crossroads Confession:CRP:5d07cf⟧

WHO   — The Crossroads Confession — kiss the earth you defiled
WHAT  — The turning of the whole novel: the proud isolato performing the most humbling public act, rejoining the human race through confession.
WHERE — CRP · Crime and Punishment  Framework inputs: Crime and Punishment (Dostoevsky, 1866)  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because redemption in Dostoevsky is not private cleverness but a public, bodily humbling — the opposite of standing above the crowd.
HOW   — By bowing in the square, kissing the defiled earth, and speaking the words ‘I killed’ where all can hear.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  Bow down, kiss the earth you have defiled, and say it aloud to everyone — the cure for standing above the crowd is to kneel in the middle of it.

